Body and voice. Vocal warmup exercises. Building of the vocal apparatus. Correct breathing. Estonian phonetics. Speaking as self-expression. Voice hygiene.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aims of the cousre are to give students skills for applying knowldege in practice; provide knowledge about interpreting different types of texts; to develop students' self-expression; to give basic knowledge about voice care and hygiene.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course students can take care of their voice; analyse the quality of voice and articulation in speaking; will be able to perform texts correctly and  with with clear articulation;  will know the principles of voice care and can use their voice properly.
